      "confidence": "high"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "loop_payload_capture_in_toggle_steps",
      "summary": "Workflow steps in startram toggle use a shared payload variable inside loop-constructed closures, so multiple steps can dispatch the same (last) payload.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/shipworkflow/startram.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/urbit_operations.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`HandleStartramToggle` builds `workflow.Step` entries inside `for _, patp := range settings.Piers`.",
        "It sets `payload := structs.WsUrbitPayload{...}` and captures `payload` directly in `Run: func() error { return startramDispatchUrbitPayloadFn(payload) }` without creating a per-iteration copy.",
        "No intermediate function boundary enforces immutability of the per-pier action arguments before the closure executes."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Construct the payload inside each closure from a per-iteration copied ship id (for example, `patpCopy := patp`) or pass a closure that takes `patpCopy` explicitly, ensuring each step captures its own input value.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "single_edit",
      "root_cause_cluster": "workflow_loop_capture"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "pass_through_seam_abstraction_bloat",
      "summary": "Runtime seam layers repeatedly use pass-through wrappers and thin duplicate types, creating low-leverage abstractions that obscure orchestration intent across modules.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/volume_writer.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/container/helpers.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/container/netdata.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_seams.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`goseg/docker/orchestration/volume_writer.go` introduces `buildCopyFileToVolumeFn` that only delegates to `requiredCopyFileToVolumeFn` without policy or translation.",
        "`volume_writer.go` aliases `writeConfigArtifactOptions = artifactwriter.WriteConfig` and wraps only to forward the call.",
        "`container/helpers.go` defines a parallel `writeConfigArtifactOptions` type and forwarding wrapper performing only shallow field mapping.",
        "`runtime_seams.go` repeatedly defines multiple function fields and option structs with repetitive nil-guard assignment logic for every operation group, while other seam packages mirror this same pattern."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Consolidate these seam layers into a small shared constructor/runtime helper with explicit policy hooks (e.g., one typed seam record and one normalization strategy), replacing repeated identity wrappers and copy-based option copying with a single coherent abstraction.",
